
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteStyle rectangle

class Cinema {
  - name: String
  - location: String
  - copies: Set<MovieCopy>
}

class Theatre {
  - id: int
  - cinema: Cinema
  - shows: Set<Show>
}

class Movie {
  - title: String
  - duration: int
}

class MovieCopy {
  - id: int
  - movie: Movie
  - cinema: Cinema
  - location: String
}

class Show {
  - id: int
  - startTime: DateTime
  - endTime: DateTime
  - theatre: Theatre
  - movie: Movie
  - published: boolean
  - status: String
}

class Reservation {
  - id: int
  - show: Show
  - customer: Customer
  - seatNumber: int
  - reservedTime: DateTime
  - isCancelled: boolean
}

class Offer {
  - id: int
  - reservation: Reservation
  - newShow: Show
  - offerTime: DateTime
  - expiresAt: DateTime
  - accepted: boolean
}

class Ticket {
  - id: int
  - show: Show
  - seatNumber: int
  - customer: Customer
  - issuedAt: DateTime
}

class Customer {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - email: String
}

' Relationships

Cinema "1" -- "0..*" Copy : has
Theatre "1" -- "1" Cinema : located in
Theatre "1" -- "0..*" Show : hosts
Movie "1" -- "0..*" MovieCopy : used by
Movie "1" -- "0..*" Show : shown in
Show "1" -- "0..*" Reservation : has
Show "1" -- "0..*" Offer : can generate
Reservation "1" -- "1" Customer : made by
Offer "1" -- "1" Reservation : related to
Offer "1" -- "1" Show : offers new seat
Show "1" -- "0..*" Ticket : has
Ticket "1" -- "1" Customer : issued to
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Reservation : makes
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Ticket : receives

@enduml

### Notes:
- This diagram uses **aggregation** and **composition** where appropriate.
- The `status` field in `Show` can be used to represent whether it's published or cancelled.
- The `Offer` class represents the alternative seat proposal for customers who cancel their reservations.
- The `Ticket` class represents physical tickets issued at the entrance, which are not cancellable.
- The `Reservation` class includes information about seat numbers, time, and cancellation status.

